BT /F2 15 Tf 54 630.00 Td (Executive Summary) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 605.00 Td (The core architecture is workable and avoids the worst command-injection mistake because Python) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 591.00 Td (  is spawned with argument arrays instead of shell interpolation. However, the platform is) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 577.00 Td (  currently vulnerable to resource exhaustion and unsafe file-processing risks. The highest-risk) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 563.00 Td (  issues are missing server-side file type validation, unbounded Python processing, no) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 549.00 Td (  child-process timeout/concurrency control, and public static exposure of processed files.) Tj ET
BT /F2 15 Tf 54 521.00 Td (1. Security Vulnerabilities) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 492.00 Td ([HIGH] Server-side upload validation is extension-only or absent) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 472.00 Td (Affected files: backend-api/middlewares/upload.js, backend-api/routes/pdfRoutes.js,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 458.00 Td (  frontend/src/components/DragDropZone.jsx.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 438.00 Td (Multer limits file size to 50 MB, but it does not validate MIME type, magic bytes, page count,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 424.00 Td (  image dimensions, or file structure. The frontend checks extensions, but client-side checks are) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 410.00 Td (  bypassable.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 390.00 Td (Risk: an attacker can upload a renamed binary, malformed PDF, image decompression bomb, or) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 376.00 Td (  Office ZIP bomb and force Python libraries to parse it.) Tj ET
